text.section:
In addition to the duties set forth elsewhere in this title, the Board shall:
Carry out the provisions of this title;
Review and comment on proposed regulations that relate to well system equipment and the construction of wells that are submitted to it before adoption by the Secretary;
Collect and account for any funds received under this title;
Keep a record of:
Each license that it issues; and
Each action it takes under § 13-310 of this title;
Require any person who practices well drilling to be covered in accordance with its regulations by a reasonable performance bond and reasonable contractor's liability insurance; and
Have an official seal.
